@startuml verifier-state-machine
title verifier_ctx_t — State Machine

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #fdfdfd
    BorderColor #555555
}

[*] --> EXPECT_INIT : verifier_init()

state EXPECT_INIT : Waiting for the first line.\nMust carry an INIT SD element\nwhose pubkey fingerprint matches.
state PROCESSING : Chain is live.\nEach line updates the chain;\nSIG lines verify signatures.
state ERROR : Unrecoverable: bad INIT,\nfingerprint mismatch, etc.\nFurther process_line() returns -1.
state DONE : verifier_finalize() called.\nNo more lines accepted.

EXPECT_INIT --> PROCESSING : valid INIT SD\n(fingerprint OK,\nchain_hash = IV)

EXPECT_INIT --> ERROR : line is not an INIT SD\n/ missing siglog SD\n/ fingerprint mismatch

PROCESSING --> PROCESSING : MSG SD\n(hash chain update)
PROCESSING --> PROCESSING : SIG SD\n(hash + verify signature;\nadd_error on mismatch)
PROCESSING --> PROCESSING : CONTINUE SD\n(segment_count++)
PROCESSING --> PROCESSING : new INIT SD\n(multi-segment file:\nstart fresh chain;\nstrict-mode warning on\nunsigned tail of prior segment)

PROCESSING --> ERROR : chain init failure\n/ hash error

EXPECT_INIT --> DONE : verifier_finalize()\n(add_error "empty file")
PROCESSING --> DONE : verifier_finalize()\n(strict-mode add_error\nif unsigned tail)

ERROR --> DONE : verifier_finalize()

note right of PROCESSING
  Recoverable errors (chain hash mismatch,
  invalid signature, sequence skew) are
  recorded via add_error() but do NOT
  drop the state out of PROCESSING.
  Only structural problems (bad INIT,
  fingerprint mismatch) transition to ERROR.
end note

DONE --> [*]

@enduml
